HEADWORD: Dagges
<hw>Dagges</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧gz)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[OE. See
<er>Dag</er> a loose end.]</ety> <def>An ornamental cutting of the edges
of garments, introduced about <sc>a. d.</sc> 1346, according to the
Chronicles of St Albans.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

